description: 1) An underground hollow with access from the ground surface or from the sea, often found in limestone areas and on rocky coastlines.2) A natural cavity, chamber or recess which leads beneath the surface of the earth, generally in a horizontal or obliquely inclined direction. It may be in the form of a passage or a gallery, its shape depending in part on the joint pattern or structure of the rock and partly on the type of process involved in its excavation. Thus, caves worn by subterranean rivers may be different in character from, and of considerably greater extent than, a sea-cave eroded by marine waves.3) A natural underground open space, generally with a connection to the surface and large enough for a person to enter. description: Any seabird of the family Diomedeidae. Some species are among the largest flying birds in the world.
name: ALBATROSS

description: Any of two species of large, flightless birds in the family Struthionidae, native to Africa.
name: OSTRICH

description: The pointed stinging organ of an animal, usually an insect, which is able to penetrate skin. Sometimes used to inject poison.
name: STINGER

description: Any of the bones forming the skeleton of a fish, especially one of the sharp slender bones attached to the backbone.
name: FISHBONE

description: The hard, white substance which forms the tusks of animals like elephants, narwhals, or walruses and is often considered a valuable material.
name: IVORY

description: The sweet, edible fruit of the date palm Phoenix dactylifera of the family Arecaceae.
name: DATE (FRUIT)

description: Any member of a large group of vascular plants in the family Filices who have neither flowers nor seeds.
name: FERN

description: The edible, berry-like fruit of a multitude of plant species in the genus Rubus of the family Rosaceae, most typically red, small and sweet.
name: RASPBERRY

description: The fruit of the pomelo tree, Citrus maxima, of the family Rutaceae, or the fruit of the grapefruit tree, Citrus x paradisi, a citrus hybrid which originated from crossing pomelos and oranges. Due to the recent origin of the grapefruit and the close genetic relatedness between both fruits, they are often not differentiated lexically.
name: GRAPEFRUIT OR POMELO

description: The feeling of being uncomfortable with attracting attention or feeling shame or guilt.
name: SHY OR ASHAMED

description: Suitable for eating because it is fully grown (of fruit and crops) or because it has been boiled, fried, grilled, etc.
name: RIPE OR COOKED

description: The partly visible orb nesting in the eye socket which contains for example pupil, retina and iris and is connected to the brain via the optic nerve.
name: EYEBALL

description: A type of forest with thick and overgrown ground vegetation, typically associated with tropical or humid climate zones.
name: JUNGLE

description: To give a loud cry out of pain, fear or excitement. The vocalisation resulted from screaming is distinct from that produced by shrieking in that it is typically characterized by a longer duration and lower pitch.
name: SCREAM (PRODUCE A CRY)

description: A large rock fragment of natural origin, usually too heavy to be moved by a single person.
name: BOULDER

description: Mauritia flexuosa, a palm tree of the family Arecaceae, common to tropical regions of South America.
name: MIRITI PALM

description: Not being brave or courageous; an attribute describing someone who is easily frightened or disheartened in the face of difficulty or danger.
name: COWARDLY
notes: yes bc brave was

description: Refusing to obey what someone in authority is requesting.
name: DISOBEDIENT

description: Used to describe a person that is attractive and pleasing in appearance.
name: HANDSOME

description: The edible and cultivated fruit of the tree Prunus dulcis in the family Rosaceae. It resembles a nut and can be sold shelled or unshelled.
name: ALMOND

description: The phase in the lunar cycle between new moon and full moon when the illuminated area increases.
name: WAXING MOON
notes: blanket yes on all things that are periods of time

description: The phase in the lunar cycle between full moon and new moon when the illuminated area decreases.
name: WANING MOON
notes: blanket yes on all things that are periods of time

description: The subjective feeling of an increased body temperature.
name: HOT (FEELING HOT)
notes: no bc not mental

description: The subjective feeling of a decreased body temperature.
name: COLD (FEELING COLD)
notes: no bc not mental

description: A situation in which a body of water is free from disturbance and without wind or waves.
name: CALM (OF SEA)

description: A very shallow flowing body of water smaller than a creek that can easily be crossed.
name: BROOK

description: The male child of the sibling of a parent of a person.
name: MALE COUSIN

description: The female child of the sibling of a parent of a person.
name: FEMALE COUSIN

description: The offspring of a stallion (male horse) and a female donkey (jenny).
name: HINNY

description: A male of the Felis catus species.
name: MALE CAT

description: Member of the species Capreolus capreolus widespread in Europe. Smaller than other deer and characterised by its red and grey-brown colour.
name: ROE DEER

description: Describing an animal that is pregnant.
name: PREGNANT (OF ANIMALS)

description: Relating to the general state of health and well-being.
name: HEALTHINESS
notes: no bc not mental

description: Describing the main meal of the day.
name: DINNER (MAIN MEAL)

description: A supporting structure for different types of constructions, e.g. houses and huts, or a construction to enclose and separate areas.
name: WALL

description: To have temporary possession of premises (apartments) or objects.
name: RENT (SOMETHING)

description: To put someone or oneself in a sitting position.
name: PUT (IN A SITTING POSITION)

description: To put someone or oneself in a standing position.
name: PUT (IN A STANDING POSITION)

description: A feeling of affection and fondness for someone.
name: LOVE (AFFECTION)

description: To have a specific name or be named something or be called something.
name: BE CALLED BY NAME

description: Describing one of the two equal parts into which something may be divided.
name: HALF (HALF OF)

description: A property describing a substance which causes the skin, membranes, or other tissue to contract. Tannins in unripe fruit are known to function as astringents.
name: ASTRINGENT

description: The distance between splayed out thumb and little finger or index finger of a human hand. Formerly used as a unit of measurement or for roughly gauging small lengths around 20 centimeters.
name: HANDSPAN

description: Bean of the plant Vicia faba, also known as fava bean. It is typically large, of a pale green colour, and edible.
name: BROAD BEAN

description: The red and typically sour berry of several evergreen shrubs in the family Ericaceae.
name: CRANBERRY

description: A large structure or building with long revolving blades or sails that is used for converting wind energy in order to produce electricity or to directly power an attached mechanical construction for grinding.
name: WINDMILL

description: One of three equal parts of a whole.
name: ONE THIRD

description: A coordinating expression that signals a contrast to what was previously said, e.g. disagreement or a further point to consider.
name: BUT

description: A feeling of ultimate disgust and a complete lack of respect towards somebody.
name: CONTEMPT

description: A feeling of sadness because something did not happen the way it was expected or did not happen at all.
name: DISAPPOINTMENT

description: A feeling of extreme but short-term happiness.
name: EXCITEMENT

description: A desire to learn about something or somebody.
name: INTEREST (FEELING)

description: A feeling caused by something unexpected.
name: SURPRISE (FEELING)

description: A feeling of extreme pleasure and excitement as a result of success or a victory.
name: TRIUMPH

description: A feeling caused by doing or watching something entertaining or funny.
name: AMUSEMENT

description: A feeling of deep respect mixed with slight fear or wonder.
name: AWE

description: The ability to direct all the attention to one thing or activity.
name: CONCENTRATION
notes: yes bc you feel it in your head

description: A feeling of uncertainty about what to do or what is happening.
name: CONFUSION

description: A feeling of being unhappy because something is missing or wrong.
name: SADNESS

description: To have an unpleasant sensation on the skin that provokes the need to scratch; to be the cause of this sensation.
name: ITCH (CAUSE ITCHING OR FEEL ITCHY)

description: To have an unpleasant sensation on the skin that provokes the need to scratch or to be the cause of this sensation; the result of itching, i.e. an unpleasant sensation on the skin, or the property of having or producing such a sensation.
name: ITCH OR ITCHY OR ITCHING

description: The calcareous covering protecting the inside of an egg.
name: EGGSHELL

description: Being in a state of not exactly knowing or understanding what is happening; bewildered; perplexed.
name: CONFUSED

description: A person, usually a woman, who helps women in childbirth and provides ante- and postnatal care.
name: MIDWIFE

description: The totality of things that someone owns; their property or belongings.
name: POSSESSIONS

description: Not succeeding in an endeavour (of persons) or to stop working as intended (of objects).
name: FAIL

description: To perceive sound with the ear, with or without paying attention to it.
name: HEAR OR LISTEN

description: The rest of a group or an unspecified quantity or number.
name: OTHER OR SOME

description: To experience an unpleasant physical sensation that is often the result of an injury, disease or other ailment; an unpleasant physical sensation itself.
name: HURT OR PAIN
notes: no bc not mental

description: Cover of the bodies of animals and plants, including the hard exterior part of mollusks, oysters, etc.
name: BARK OR SHELL

description: An intervention in a pregnancy by removal or expulsion of an embryo or fetus resulting in termination of the pregnancy.
name: ABORTION

description: A person who is affected by alcoholism in that they frequently drink alcohol which leads to addiction.
name: ALCOHOLIC (PERSON)

description: A bodily reaction due to a hypersensitivity to an antigen or a pathological immunological reaction to substances, situations, or physical states.
name: ALLERGY

description: To feel uneasiness of mind caused by anxiety.
name: ANXIOUS

description: Having been affected by rust.
name: RUSTY

description: A person who commits murder.
name: MURDERER

description: A pale yellowish-brown color usually of hair.
name: BLOND

description: A food prepared from ground, roasted cocoa beans and often used to make candy.
name: CHOCOLATE

description: The fact or state of knowing something or being familiar with a certain type of technique.
name: KNOWLEDGE

description: A person who committed a crime.
name: CRIMINAL

description: A person who is medically trained and licensed to practice the prevention, diagnosis, and treatment of diseases, injuries, and malformations of the teeth, jaws, and mouth.
name: DENTIST

description: A state of feeling sad that can become a chronic illness.
name: DEPRESSION

description: The hardest known mineral on earth, consisting of crystalline carbon.
name: DIAMOND

description: To form a mental image of (something not present).
name: IMAGINE

description: A hostile encounter, such as a battle or combat.
name: FIGHT (COMBAT)

description: A handgun with the chamber integral to its gun barrel.
name: PISTOL

description: A showy flower of any of a genus (Rosa of the family Rosaceae, the rose family).
name: ROSE

description: To make a lot of noise.
name: NOISY

description: Enduring difficult situations or a long waiting time with an even temper.
name: PATIENT
notes: no bc only general tendency not a state

description: Becoming irritable in difficult situations or during long waiting times.
name: IMPATIENT
notes: no bc only general tendency not a state

description: Any large and hairy spider, typically of the Theraphosidae family, although some other spider species are subsumed under this name as well.
name: TARANTULA

description: No person; not one member out of a group of people.
name: NOBODY

description: Mammals of the family Mephitidae, typically found in North and South America. These animals are known for their ability to spray attackers with a strong-smelling liquid.
name: SKUNK

description: To perform an incision or chop something.
name: CUT OR HACK

description: A child of someone's brother or sister.
name: NEPHEW OR NIECE

description: The outer opening of the ear.
name: EARHOLE

description: To come into possession of something, usually with an effort.
name: ACQUIRE (SOMETHING)

description: To have enough money to get something.
name: AFFORD

description: To fasten one thing to another.
name: ATTACH

description: To notice or recognize something that is not particularly obvious.
name: DETECT

description: To make a deep loud cry (of lions and comparable wild animals); to make a deep loud cry, usually out of anger (of humans).
name: ROAR
notes: yes by analogy to scream

description: The physical world including all living things as well as the land and the seas.
name: NATURE

description: To take or get something that was offered by someone.
name: ACCEPT

description: To use violence with the intention to harm.
name: ATTACKING

description: Moving carelessly or gracelessly, causing things to break or get knocked over.
name: CLUMSY

description: To domesticate an animal, bird, etc.; to make them used to living with and/or working for humans.
name: TAMING

description: To have great confidence in someone that he or she is sincere, honest, and will not deliberately inflict any harm.
name: TRUST (SOMEBODY)
notes: yes bc feel it in your head

description: To show understanding for somebody's problems or hurt feelings.
name: SYMPATHIZE
notes: yes bc feel it in your head

description: To meet someone or discover something, usually unexpectedly.
name: ENCOUNTER (MEET)

description: A male parent of a woman.
name: FATHER (OF A WOMAN)
notes: yes bc between me and grandparents

description: A male parent of a man.
name: FATHER (OF A MAN)
notes: yes bc between me and grandparents

description: A female parent of a woman.
name: MOTHER (OF A WOMAN)
notes: yes bc between me and grandparents

description: A female parent of a man.
name: MOTHER (OF A MAN)
notes: yes bc between me and grandparents

description: Offspring of one's son.
name: GRANDCHILD (SON'S OFFSPRING)

description: The child of one's spouse and his or her previous partner.
name: STEPCHILD
notes: not kin see murdock

description: The milk of cows.
name: COW MILK

description: The milk of humans.
name: BREAST MILK

description: The act of coughing or the sound of coughing.
name: COUGH (ACT OF COUGHING)

description: Having a light greenish blue as its color.
name: TURQUOISE

description: An emotional state of being proud.
name: PRIDE

description: An emotional state of sensual gratification or frivolous amusement.
name: PLEASURE

description: The personal supreme spirit of evil often represented in Christian belief as the tempter of humankind, the leader of all apostate angels, and the ruler of hell.
name: DEVIL

description: (Not to confuse with gourd) a plant from the family Bignoniaceae, native to tropical America. It has a form of a small tree, producing fruit of the globular shape. It is also known under the name of Crescentia cujete and its fruits are mostly used to make utensils, containers, and musical instruments.
name: CALABASH

description: A species of palm, also know as Bactris gasipaes, native to the tropical forests of Central and South America.
name: PEACH PALM

description: Either a species of trees in the family Rubiaceae native to the tropical forests of Americas or its fruit (also referred to as “genipap”). A Genipa tree typically has large smooth or hairy leaves and ovoid-shaped fruit with large and flat seeds.
name: GENIPA

description: Any of the 47 sedentary, ground-dwelling bird species of the order Tinamiformes found in Central and South America. It bears a strong resemblance to patridges but has limited flight capability.
name: TINAMOU

description: A freshwater species of fish belonging to the family Serrasalmidae and related to piranha.
name: PACU
